include ../common/collapse.pug

mixin stepHtml(step, stepName, isOpen)
  .step-item
    +collapseItemHtml(`<span class='label' data-step-number='${step}'>${stepName}</span>`, null, isOpen)
      block

.step-container.container
  +collapse('validator-steps-guide')
    +stepHtml('1', 'Create your account', 'true')
      p Download the Incognito app.
      .row-img 
        .img.install-app-img
          a(href='https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.incognito.wallet', target='blank')
            img(src=require('../../image/wallet/ch google play.svg'), alt='chplay-app')
        .img.install-app-img
          a(href='https://apps.apple.com/us/app/incognito-crypto-wallet/id1475631606?ls=1', target='blank')
            img(src=require('../../image/wallet/app store.svg'), alt='ios-app')
      p Open the app and tap on
        | 
        span.highlight YOU
        |.
        | Copy
        | 
        span.highlight YOUR INCOGNITO ADDRESS
        | 
        |and
        | 
        span.highlight YOUR PRIVATE KEY
        | 
        | (keep them safe!).  You’ll need them in STEP 3 and 5.

      img(src=require('../../image/become_validator/view_account_setting.png'), alt='view_account_setting')
      img(src=require('../../image/become_validator/view_your_keys.png'), alt='view_your_keys')
      img(src=require('../../image/become_validator/copy_your_keys.png'), alt='copy_your_keys')

    +stepHtml('2', 'Set up your node')
      p You can run Incognito on a low-cost server.  If you don’t have a server yet, it’s really simple and takes just a couple of minutes.  You can set up an account with a VPS provider or a cloud service provider like
        | 
        a(href='https://www.digitalocean.com', target='blank') DigitalOcean
        |,
        | 
        a(href='https://www.linode.com/', target='blank') Linode
        | 
        | or
        | 
        a(href='https://www.vultr.com/', target='blank') Vultr.
      
      p The minimum server requirements are
        | 
        span.highlight 2GB RAM, 2 CPUs
        |, and
        | 
        span.highlight 50GB SSD.
        | 
        |For example, if you use AWS, a
        | 
        span.highlight t3.small instance
        | 
        | is sufficient.
      p Save
        | 
        span.highlight YOUR SERVER EXTERNAL IP ADDRESS.
        | 
        | You’ll need it in STEP 4.

    +stepHtml('3', 'Run Incognito')
      p Install 
        |
        a(href='https://docs.docker.com/install/', target='blank') Docker.
      p Open Terminal and enter the command line below to download 
        | 
        span.script run.sh
      p 
        span.script.copiable(data-copy-value='curl -LO https://incognito.org/run.sh') curl -LO https://incognito.org/run.sh
      p Edit
        | 
        span.script run.sh
        | 
        | and replace
        | 
        span.script xxx
        | 
        | with
        | 
        span.script YOUR PRIVATE KEY
        |
        |(from STEP 1).
      img(src=require('../../image/become_validator/edit_runsh.png'), alt='edit_runsh')
      p Then, enter the command line below to start Incognito.
      p
        span.script.copiable(data-copy-value='bash run.sh') bash run.sh
      
      p
        span If you see the following errors, just ignore them.  You’re doing good.
        br
        span.quote Error: No such container: inc_miner
        br
        span.quote Error: No such container: inc_kovan
        br
        span.quote Error response from daemon: network with name inc_net already exists
      
      p For the curious, because Incognito is integrated with Ethereum (so you can send ETH and ERC20 tokens privately), its error messages show up here.  There’s nothing much we can do about it. Move on.

    +stepHtml('4', 'Monitor your node')
      p You can easily monitor your Incognito nodes right from your phone.
      
      img(src=require('../../image/become_validator/manage_node.png'), alt='manage_node')
      img(src=require('../../image/become_validator/add_virtual_node.png'), alt='add_virtual_node')
      img(src=require('../../image/become_validator/add_virtual_node_form.png'), alt='add_virtual_node_form')

    +stepHtml('5', 'Request free Privacy (PRV)')
      p Privacy (PRV) is the native coin of the Incognito Network.  To become a validator and help build the network, you’ll need to stake the minimum 1,750 PRV.  It’s easy to request free PRV.  Follow these steps:
        ol
          li Make a public post on either Facebook or Twitter that includes
            | 
            span.highlight https://incognito.org/YOUR_INCOGNITO_ADDRESS
            | 
            |(from STEP 1).
            br
            br
            span For example:
            p.quote "I’m going to be a validator for the Incognito network. My address is https://incognito.org/1Uv3CsGLj7Ue6YoftT2XvMPrLcpETWgDPu9XQ3rF8FgZKMtwfkGPbQ1nRxtyhSVs7duQ"
            br
          li Then, copy and paste the URL of that social post to the Incognito Telegram channel
            | 
            a(href='https://t.me/incognitochain', target='blank') https://t.me/incognitochain.
            | 
            | That’s it! 1,750 PRV will be added to your wallet. If your PRV has not arrived after 12 hours, please dm @annie_incognito for support.

    +stepHtml('6', 'Stake')
      p Almost there! Now, that you’ve got PRV, all you have to do is stake. Remember, you need to stake at least 1,750 PRV to begin earning rewards.
      img(src=require('../../image/become_validator/node_want_to_stake.png'), alt='node_want_to_stake')
      img(src=require('../../image/become_validator/start_staking.png'), alt='start_staking')
      img(src=require('../../image/become_validator/stake.png'), alt='stake')
      
  p Congrats! You’re officially part of the network. Welcome to Incognito :)
  p We welcome any questions, comments, or feedback. Or just reach out to chat. We’re on telegram pretty much all the time:
    | 
    a(href='https://t.me/incognitochain', target='blank') https://t.me/incognitochain
    |, or do it the old fashioned way and send an email to
    | 
    a(href='mailto:go@incognito.org') go@incognito.org.